    "source": "the-wine-bible-karen-macneil.pdf_page_47",
    "contenu": "The document discusses viticulture and the significant role climate plays in grape cultivation and wine production. Here's a structured breakdown of the content:\n\n---\n\n**Title: Prison et Paradis**  \n*Author: Colette*\n\n**Quote:**  \n“What single cloudless day, what soft late rainfall decides that a vintage shall be great among the others? Human care can do almost nothing towards it. It is all celestial wizardry, the orbits of planets, sunspots....”\n\n**Introduction to Viticulture in Wine Production:**  \nIn this chapter, the discussion revolves around wine viewed through the lens of grape cultivation. The text emphasizes the dynamic and complex interplay of various factors in vineyard environments:\n- Climate\n- Soil type\n- Grape variety and clone\n- Rootstock and spacing considerations\n\nThese factors combine synesthetically, influencing the aroma, flavor, body, and finish of wine, celebrating the unique individuality and intricacies of each vineyard's nuances. The underlying theme acknowledges the profundity and diversity within viticulture, highlighting the compelling nature of wines not because they are the same, but because each possesses distinctive traits.\n\n**Section: Climate**  \n**Key Points:**\n- **Role of Climate:** The climate fundamentally determines the feasibility of grape growing by influencing temperatures where vines thrive or stay dormant.\n- **Temperature Specifics:**\n  - Vines begin to grow when the temperature is around 50°F (approximately 10°C).\n  - Optimal growth is observed when temperatures range from 63°F to 68°F (17°C to 20°C).\n- **Growth Cycle:**\n  - Vines start budding and flowering when conditions are right. Flowering is essential, as it leads to the formation of grape berries.\n  - Up to 85% of a vine's flowers can fail even under good conditions, a phenomenon known as \"shatter.\"\n- **Temperature and Growth:**\n  - Vines flourish best when temperatures range from the mid-80s (about 28°C to 30°C).\n\nThe section concludes by emphasizing the critical growth phases of vines and the overpowering influence of climate on these processes.\n\n--- \n\nThis structured analysis captures the essence of the document, focusing on how climate impacts wine production through viticulture. The document integrates scientific details with a contemplative view on the natural processes that define the quality and uniqueness of wine."
